/*
  ============================================================
  BIRTICS - WRO FUTURE ENGINEERS 2026
  FULL COMPETITION BASELINE CODE
  ============================================================

  Hardware:
  - ESP32 DevKit
  - L298N Channel B
  - Rear DC motor
  - Front steering servo
  - 3 x VL6180X ToF sensors
  - 2 x TCS3200 color sensors
  - MPU6050 gyroscope/accelerometer on the shared I2C expansion board

  Confirmed GPIO:
  L298N ENB  -> GPIO26
  L298N IN3  -> GPIO14
  L298N IN4  -> GPIO27

  Servo      -> GPIO18

  I2C SDA    -> GPIO21
  I2C SCL    -> GPIO22

  Front XSHUT -> GPIO25
  Left XSHUT  -> GPIO32
  Right XSHUT -> GPIO33

  TCS3200 shared:
  S0 -> GPIO4
  S1 -> GPIO16
  S2 -> GPIO17
  S3 -> GPIO5

  Ground color OUT -> GPIO34
  Front color OUT  -> GPIO35

  Start button:
  ESP32 BOOT button -> GPIO0

  Required libraries:
  - Adafruit VL6180X
  - ESP32Servo
  - MPU6050_light


  ELECTRICAL SAFETY:
  - MPU6050 and VL6180X modules: use 3.3V unless your exact breakout
    board explicitly includes a regulator/level shifting.
  - ESP32 GPIO34 and GPIO35 are input-only and are NOT 5V tolerant.
  - If a TCS3200 is powered from 5V, use a level shifter or divider on OUT.
    Safer direct ESP32 setup: power the TCS3200 logic from 3.3V.
  - The battery switch is wired in series with battery positive; it has
    no software pin and therefore requires no code.
  - Servo power problems must be fixed electrically. Code cannot protect
    a servo that is being driven into a mechanical stop by unstable power.

  IMPORTANT:
  1. Press BOOT only after ESP32 has finished booting.
  2. Do not hold BOOT while switching the ESP32 on.
  3. Calibrate servo, colors, distances and timing on the real field.
  ============================================================
*/

